Place brisket, onion, garlic and cloves in large Dutch oven. Add water to cover. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until tender. Drain brisket, cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours. To prepare glaze, combine apple jelly, wine, mustard, green onions, salt, pepper and curry powder in small saucepan and heat until jelly melts, stirring occasionally. Place brisket in shallow roasting pan. Brush with glaze and heat in 325 degree oven 45 minutes, basting frequently with glaze. Place brisket on heated serving platter and garnish with parsley and tomato roses. Carve brisket into thin slices and serve with remaining glaze.